    <H1>Introduction</H1><DIV class="s1">
      <P>
        Any OS that can provide a J2SE environment could be a host to Jesktop and <A href="http://www.nanocontainer.org">NanoContainer</A>.  That said, there are not many.  Manufacturers of lightweight and RTOSs have a fixation for Personal Java or J2ME on the KVM :-(
      </P>
    </DIV>
    <H1>Full blown</H1><DIV class="s1">
      <P>
        Windows and Linux are supported already.
      </P>
    </DIV>
    <H1>For the Future</H1><DIV class="s1">
      <P>
        AtheOS, QNX, VxWorks, Elate, (TODO).  It kinda really depends on the availablity of J2SE for those platforms and Ant supporting them.
      </P>    
    </DIV>
